    "mk.graphStats(keywords)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mk.dropEdges(keywords, minWeight = 10, dropSelfLoops = True) \n",
    "mk.dropNodesByDegree(keywords, minDegree = 1, useWeight = False)\n",
    "\n",
    "keywordsGiant = max(nx.connected_component_subgraphs(keywords), key=len)\n",
    "mk.graphStats(keywordsGiant)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "eig = nx.eigenvector_centrality(keywordsGiant)\n",
    "size = [2000 * eig[node] for node in keywordsGiant]\n",
    "\n",
    "nx.draw_spring(keywordsGiant, with_labels = False, node_size = size, \n",
    "               node_color = \"#FFFFFF\", edge_color = \"#D4D5CE\", alpha = .95)\n",
    "plt.savefig('figures/network_keywords.pdf')"
   ]

    "two_mode = RC1014.networkTwoMode('keywords', 'authorsFull') \n",
    "mk.dropEdges(two_mode, minWeight = 3, dropSelfLoops = True) \n",
    "mk.dropNodesByDegree(two_mode, minDegree = 1, useWeight = False)\n",
    "\n",
    "two_mode = max(nx.connected_component_subgraphs(two_mode), key=len)\n",
    "mk.graphStats(two_mode)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,

   },

    "size = [2000 * deg[node] for node in two_mode]\n",
    "\n",

    "               node_color = '#FFFFFF', edge_color = \"#D4D5CE\", alpha = .95)"

   "source": [
    "# Interactive Network Visualizations with *mkD3*"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To change the type of network that is being visualized, you can change two variables in the next cell.\n",
    "- **`networkType`** should be set to `\"Citation\"`, `\"CoCitation\"`, or `\"CoAuthor\"`.     \n",
    "- **`nodeType`** should be set to `\"full\"`, `\"author\"`, `\"journal\"`, or `\"year\"`. (`\"full\"` nodes are individual articles or books)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<a href=\"mkD3_static/network.html\">Open network graph</a>"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.HTML object>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Variables to Set\n",
    "# ****************\n",
    "networkType = \"CoCitation\"\n",
    "nodeType = \"full\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create the Network\n",
    "# ******************\n",
    "if networkType == \"CoCitation\":\n",
    "    net = RC1014.networkCoCitation(nodeType = nodeType, coreOnly=True)\n",
    "    directed = False\n",
    "#     partition = community.best_partition(net)\n",
    "elif networkType == \"CoAuthor\":\n",
    "    net = RC1014.networkCoAuthor()\n",
    "    directed = False\n",
    "#     partition = community.best_partition(net)\n",
    "elif networkType == \"Citation\":\n",
    "    net = RC1014.networkCitation(nodeType=nodeType, coreOnly=True)\n",
    "    directed = True\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"Please ensure networkType has been set to one of the accepted values\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Simplify the Network\n",
    "# ********************\n",
    "mk.dropEdges(net, minWeight = 2, dropSelfLoops = True) \n",
    "\n",
    "net.remove_nodes_from(nx.isolates(net)) # Remove nodes which are isolates\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add Node Data\n",
    "# *************\n",
    "if not directed: \n",
    "    partition = community.best_partition(net)\n",
    "    betweenness = nx.betweenness_centrality(net)\n",
    "    for n in net.nodes():\n",
    "        betw = round(betweenness[n], 3)\n",
    "        comm = partition[n]\n",
    "        net.add_node(n, community=comm, betweenness=betw)\n",
    "else: \n",
    "    betweenness = nx.betweenness_centrality(net)\n",
    "    for n in net.nodes():\n",
    "        betw = round(betweenness[n], 3)\n",
    "        net.add_node(n, betweenness=betw)\n",
    "\n",
    "mk.writeGraph(net, \"generated_datasets/network\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create Link to Heatmap\n",
    "from IPython.display import display, HTML\n",
    "display(HTML('<a href=\"mkD3_static/network.html\">Open network graph</a>'))"
   ]
  },
